Mallam Isa Funtua, a newspapers patron and President Muhammadu Buhari’s influential ally, is dead. He died in Abuja while undergoing a routine medical check-up. He was 78 years old. He reportedly suffered a massive heart attack during the medical check-up. He was the founder of the defunct Democrat newspaper in Kaduna. Funtua was also water resources minister in the Second Republic. By Martha Agas Jos - The Northern Governors Forum has described the death of Mallam Isma’ila Isa Funtua, a life patron of the International Press Institute and the Newspaper Proprietors Association of Nigeria, as painful. The Chairman of the forum and governor of Plateau, Simon Lalong, in a condolence message… July 21, 2020 In "Politics" By Kingsley Okoye Abuja - President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan has described as a painful loss the death of Malam Isma’ila Isa Funtua on July 20. Lawan in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media, Ola Awoniyi on Tuesday expressed his heartfelt condolences to family of the late… July 21, 2020 In "Politics" A vote for APC in the coming presidential election won't be a vote for Buhari; it would be a vote for an evil, greedy, corrupt, provincial, and reactionary cabal made up of Mamman Daura, Abba Kyari, Isa Funtua and their minions who are currently perpetrating a stratospheric theft of the… January 23, 2019 In "Social Media Feeds"